enous land dispossession and environmental injustice for centuries. Rooting in a Useless Land explores how archaeology, practiced within communities, can restore history and strengthen relationships built on contested ground.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCelebrity chefszMexicozYaxcabá. 0aCelebrity chefszMexicozYaxcabá. 0aEnvironmental justicezMexicozYaxcabá. 0aEnvironmental justicezMexicozYaxcabá. 0aFarmerszMexicozYaxcabá. 0aFarmerszMexicozYaxcabá. 0aSustainable developmentzMexicozYaxcabá. 0aSustainable developmentzMexicozYaxcabá. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520395886?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520395886423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520395886/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles